messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /api/users/auth

- allMethodsAllowed: false

- Methods accepted (based on code):
  - HEAD: false
  - POST: true
  - OPTIONS: false
  - TRACE: false
  - GET: false
  - PUT: false
  - DELETE: false
  - PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In server.js the user routes are mounted with app.use('/api/users', userRoutes), so every route defined in routes/userRoutes.js is prefixed with /api/users.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the route that wires authUser is defined as router.post('/auth', authUser), so the controller is reachable at POST /api/users/auth (no path parameters).
- The controller file controllers/userController.js also documents the route as POST /api/users/auth and implements the login logic.
- Only a POST handler is registered for this path in the code. There are no explicit handlers for HEAD, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS or TRACE for this path in the provided files, so those methods are marked false.
- (Per the instructions I did not assume implicit framework behavior such as Express automatically providing HEAD responses for GET handlers; only explicit handlers present in the code were considered.)
